                    <p><br></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">This payment policy (&quot;Payment Policy&quot;) governs the Payment Services (as defined in the Speakede Terms) provided by Speakede to you. Capitalized terms (including the term &quot;Speakede&quot;) used but not defined in this Payment Policy have the meanings ascribed to such terms in our Terms of Service, which is available&nbsp;</span><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/u/0/d/1U10mGJaO7_zHE64OCaGLQK1ZXA2kCUMvlWvbCpHpiww/edit"><u><span style="color:#1155cc;font-size:10.5pt;">here</span></u></a><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;(the &quot;Speakede Terms&quot;).</span></p>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <hr>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">1. Key Terms for Payment Services</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Speakede Tokens&apos;&apos; means the virtual currency purchased from Speakede, which can be used solely on the Speakede Platform to purchase Tutor Services, and does not have any value outside of the Speakede Platform. All Tutor Services on the Speakede Platform are paid for with Speakede Tokens.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Lesson Fees&quot; or &quot;Package Fees&quot; means the amounts that are due and payable by a Learner for confirmed language lessons that have been given by a Tutor. The Tutor alone, and not Speakede, is responsible setting the amount of the Lesson Fees or Package Fees.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Service Fees&quot; means the fees Speakede charges to the Tutor when using Speakede Connection Services.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Learner Wallet&quot; means an account created by a Learner to purchase Speakede Tokens that will be spent on the Speakede Platform. Speakede Tokens in a Learner Wallet can be used to pay for Tutor Services provided by Tutors, and other services offered by or through the Speakede Platform.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Payment Method&quot; means a method or service available on the Speakede Platform for a Learner to purchase Speakede Tokens, such as credit card, debit card, Pay with bank, Pay with transfer.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Tutor Wallet&quot; means an account created by Tutors to receive payment for Tutor Services.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Withdrawal Method&quot; means a method or service available on the Speakede Platform for a Tutor to receive cash in the exchange for Speakede Tokens, such as PayPal, and other third party payment providers.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">2. Lesson Contract</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Upon confirmation of Tutor Services, time, and price by both the Learner and the Tutor, such Learner and Tutor shall be considered as entering into a contract, pursuant to which the Learner agrees to purchase, and the Tutor agrees to deliver, the Tutor Services (the &quot;Lesson Contract&quot;). You agree not to enter into any contractual provisions that conflict with the Speakede Terms or other Speakede Policies. The Learner and Tutor each covenant and agree to act with good faith and fair dealing in performance of the Lesson Contract. Furthermore, the Learner and Tutor each acknowledge and agree that the value, reputation, and goodwill of the Speakede Platform depends on their performance of the foregoing covenants and agreements. The Learner and the Tutor therefore agree that Speakede has the right to take such actions with respect to the Lesson Contract, including without limitation suspension, termination, or legal actions, as Speakede in its sole discretion deems necessary to protect the value, reputation, and goodwill of the Speakede Platform.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">3. Financial Terms for Learners</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">For Learners, you must use Speakede Tokens to purchase Tutor Services from a Tutor. Speakede provides each Learner with a Learner Wallet to hold the Speakede Tokens.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.1 Purchasing Speakede Tokens</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">In order to acquire Speakede Tokens, you may use a Payment Method to pay for the desired amount of Speakede Tokens through your Speakede Account. By providing Speakede with the required information for the applicable Payment Method, you authorize us to charge for the amounts you selected on the payment page of your Speakede Account. Following a successful transaction, your Learner Wallet will have the corresponding amount of Speakede Tokens. You acknowledge and agree that the Speakede Token you purchased will be used to pay Speakede or Tutor for the services on the Speakede Platform. If you are a Company, Speakede Token acquired by you may be allocated between the Company Employees&rsquo; Speakede Account.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.2 No Refunds on Authorized Payments</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Authorized payments are final. No refunds will be given for Speakede Tokens purchased.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.3 Third Party Payment Method Fees</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">When purchasing Speakede Tokens, you may be charged additional fees by the third party that provides the applicable Payment Method. These fees are not under Speakede&apos;s control, and Speakede disclaims all liability in this regard. Whatever Payment Method you use may be subject to additional terms and conditions, which we recommend that you review before using such Payment Method.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.4 Canceled Lesson Requests</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If a Lesson Request is canceled by the Learner, declined by the Tutor, or expires (not confirmed by the Tutor within the request period), you will receive a 100% refund in the form of Speakede credits to the student&rsquo;s student wallet.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.5 Confirmation of Lessons</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">As a Learner, when you confirm a Lesson was successful, you confirm that the Tutor has completed the applicable Tutor Services fully and satisfactorily, and you are instructing Speakede to transfer the applicable Speakede Tokens from your Learner Wallet to the Tutor&rsquo;s Tutor Wallet.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.6 Feedback and Ratings on Lessons</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">As a Learner, when you confirm a Lesson was successful, you may be asked to leave feedback and a rating for the Tutor. Leaving feedback or a rating is optional. However, if you do so, you agree that your feedback must be genuine and honest, and will not commit fraud, spam, insult, harass, threaten, or otherwise misuse the feedback system.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">You agree to report violations or abuses of our rating and feedback system by contacting Customer Support, and agree not to take any actions that undermine the integrity of the feedback system.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">4. Financial Terms for Tutors</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">For Tutors, you must use Speakede Tokens to receive payment for Tutor Services from Learners. Speakede provides each Tutor with a &quot;Tutor Wallet &apos;&apos; to hold the Speakede Tokens and to convert Speakede Tokens to cash.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.1 Accepting Lesson Requests</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Tutors will receive requests for Lessons from Learners (&quot;Lesson Requests&quot;). By accepting a Lesson Request, you agree to provide the Lesson to the Learner at the date and time as described in the applicable Lesson Request. You can choose to decline any Lesson Request. If you do not respond, the Lesson Request will automatically expire.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.2 Cancellations of Lesson Requests</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">As a Tutor, you acknowledge and agree that Speakede may in its sole discretion cancel a confirmed Lesson Request pursuant to Speakede Terms and other Speakede Policies. You further acknowledge and agree that Speakede and the relevant Learner will not have any liability for such cancellations or refunds.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.3 Speakede Commission Fees</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede collects commission fees when successful completion of a Lesson is confirmed by the Learner. For each successfully completed Lesson, the commission is 25% of the total cost of such Lesson (&quot;Commission Fee&quot;). The Commission Fee will be deducted upon the transfer of Speakede Tokens to the Tutor&apos;s Tutor Wallet.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">The balance shown in the Tutor Wallet is the full balance after all fees have been deducted. Amounts may be rounded up or down as described in the &quot;Rounding Off&quot; section below.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">To the extent any refunds are issued to a Learner, no Commission Fees will be charged to the Tutor with respect to Speakede Tokens that are refunded back to the Learner.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.4 No Circumvention of Commission Fees</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Tutors shall not to engage in any action or activity meant to circumvent the Commission Fees, with such actions or activities including, but not limited to, the following: (i) suggesting, soliciting, or accepting payment outside of the Speakede Platform, or by other means other than through the Payment Services; or (ii) reporting or listing an inaccurate price for a Lesson on the Speakede Platform, or charging a fee for a Lesson that is different from the amount agreed between Learner and Tutor.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.5 Withdrawal of Funds</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">When withdrawing Speakede Tokens, you may be charged additional fees by the third party that provides the applicable Withdrawal Method. These fees are not under Speakede&apos;s control, and Speakede disclaims all liability in this regard. Whatever Withdrawal Method you use may be subject to additional terms and conditions, which we recommend that you review before using such Withdrawal Method.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.6 Withholding or Delaying Disbursement of Funds</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If Speakede determines that a Tutor&apos;s actions may have resulted or will result in a significant number of disputes, refunds or other claims from Learners who purchased such Tutor&rsquo;s Lessons, Speakede reserves the right to delay or stop the disbursement of all funds accrued in such Tutor&apos;s Tutor Wallet. If Speakede reasonably concludes that a Tutor has violated the Speakede Terms or other Speakede Policies, Speakede may refuse to disburse the funds accrued in such Tutor&apos;s Tutor Wallet and debit such funds from the Tutor Wallet.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">4.7 Rounding Off</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede may, in its sole discretion, round up or round down amounts that are payable from or to Tutors or Learners to the nearest whole functional base unit in which the currency is denominated (e.g. to the nearest Dollar/ Naira); for example Speakede may round up an amount of NGN 101.50 to NGN 102.00, and may round down an amount of NGN101.49 to NGN 101.00.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">5. Lesson Packages</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">A Tutor may offer Learners, and Learners may purchase from a Tutor, more than one Lesson in a single package (each such lesson package, a &quot;Lesson Package&quot;). Learners are expecting to complete all Lessons in the Lesson Packages within six (6) months of the purchase date (the &quot;Package Expiration Date&quot;). If there are any remaining Lessons that have not been completed on or before the Package Expiration Date, Speakede will send reminders to both the Learner and the Tutor prior to the applicable Package Expiration Date. The Learner may extend the Lesson Package on the Learner&rsquo;s Speakede Account before the applicable Package Expiration Date, but if the Learner fails to do so, then all remaining Speakede Tokens in the package will be sent to the Tutor, minus Speakede&apos;s Commission Fees.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">6. Taxes</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Tutors shall be solely responsible for determining their applicable tax related duties in connection with the income obtained from their Tutor Services, and shall also be solely responsible for remitting to the relevant authority any applicable taxes that need to be paid. Speakede cannot and does not offer tax-related advice to any Members.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">7. Speakede Tokens Policies</span></strong></h5>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">7.1 Speakede Tokens are not Bank Deposits</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">You acknowledge that: (1) Speakede is not a bank, and Learner Wallets and Tutor Wallets are a payment service rather than a banking service; and (2) Speakede is not acting as a trustee or fiduciary with respect to your funds, but is acting only as an agent and custodian. (3) SPEAKEDE IS NOT A BANK, AND AMOUNTS TRANSFERRED THROUGH OR STORED IN STUDENT WALLETS OR TEACHER WALLETS ARE NOT INSURED DEPOSITS.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">7.2 Speakede Tokens Expiration Policy</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede Token Expiration Policy Speakede Tokens in a Speakede Account will be valid for so long as the Member remains active on Speakede. If any Member&rsquo;s Speakede Account has been inactive for more than twelve (12) months, the Speakede Tokens will expire. Tokens can be reactivated by contacting Speakede customer support with a reactivation request, with the condition that the credits have expired for less than 12 months. Tokens can be reactivated only one time, and will be valid for 12 months after the reactivation. Any activity in the credits will extend the expiration date of the credits an additional 12 months.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">7.3 Foreign Exchange Risk</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede Tokens are tied to US Dollars for International Learners and Naira for learners in Nigeria. Speakede is not responsible for currency fluctuations that occur when billing or crediting a credit or debit card denominated in a currency other than US Dollars, nor is Speakede responsible for currency fluctuations that occur when receiving or sending payment via third party payment services when purchasing Speakede Tokens or withdrawing an Speakede Token balance.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">7.4 Speakede Tokens Limitations</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede Tokens are valid only when purchased on the Speakede Platform or through authorized Speakede partners. Speakede Tokens in the form of Speakede gift cards or vouchers cannot be resold or redeemed for cash. Speakede Tokens redeemed from gift cards or vouchers purchased through unofficial sources or channels are subject to cancellation without notice.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">8. Speakede&apos;s Rights Regarding Speakede Accounts and Funds</span></strong></h5>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">8.1 Security and Financial Fraud</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">As a security measure, Speakede may impose transaction limits on some or all Learners and Tutors relating to the value of any transaction or disbursement, the cumulative value of all transactions or disbursements during a period of time, or the number of transactions per day or other period of time. We will impose these limits before any services are rendered if we determine it is necessary for security reasons or the prevention of fraud.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede reserves the right to void Speakede Token purchases if purchases are found to be fraudulent. This includes Speakede Tokens that have been redeemed from fraudulent Speakede gift card purchases.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">8.2 Reservation of Rights for Erroneous Transactions</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede reserves the right to seek reimbursement from any Tutor or Learner, if Speakede, in its sole discretion, determines that erroneous or duplicate transactions have occurred. Speakede may obtain such reimbursement by deducting from future payments owed to such Tutor, by reversing any Speakede Tokens to such Tutor&apos;s Tutor Wallet, or by seeking reimbursement from such Tutor by any other lawful means.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">8.3 Prohibition on Friendly Fraud</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">&quot;Friendly Fraud&quot; is when a person initiates a fraud dispute with a payment provider, claiming that their credit card (or other payment method) was not intended to be used. Because Speakede does not offer refunds, users that disagree with the policy have tried to use Friendly Fraud to receive a refund.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">This type of behavior is illegal and prohibited by all payment providers. Speakede also strictly opposes Friendly Fraud. If Friendly Fraud is discovered, the Learner&apos;s Speakede Account and Learner Wallet will be deactivated, purchased credits will be confiscated, and the Learner will be noted as a financial security risk.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">In the case of honest mistakes, Speakede can reverse the transaction. We strongly advise Learners to contact Speakede Customer Support to resolve any financial disputes.</span></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">9. Prohibitions</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">In addition to complying with the restrictions regarding improper use of the Speakede Platform described in Section 11 (Restrictions) of the Speakede Terms, you understand and agree that you are solely responsible for compliance with any applicable laws, rules, regulations, and tax obligations that may apply to you in connection with the use of the Payment Services. In addition, you may not and you agree that you will not:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Violate any local, state, provincial, national, or other law or regulation, or any order of a court, such as money laundering and internet fraud or theft;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Use the Payment Services for any commercial or other purposes that are not expressly permitted by this Payment Policy;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Use the Payment Services to transmit, distribute, post or submit any information concerning any other person or entity, including without limitation, personal contact information or credit, debit, calling card or account numbers, or photographs of others without their permission;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Register any Payment Method or Withdrawal Method with your Speakede account that is not yours or you do not have authorization to use;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Attempt to probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of any Speakede system or network or breach any security or authentication measures;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Avoid, bypass, remove, deactivate, impair, descramble, or otherwise circumvent any technological measure implemented by Speakede or any other third party (including another Member) to protect the Payment Services;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Forge any TCP/IP packet header or any part of the header information in any email or newsgroup posting, or in any way use the Payment Services to send altered, deceptive or false source-identifying information;</span></p>
                        </li>
